      "content": "Yeah, so the way that our pricing works basically we charge, we charge $105 an hour per mover. So this will be a two mover team, so that'd be a $210 hourly rate included in that hourly rate. We will wrap everything and blankets and shrink wrap we will take apart the bed frame, put it back together anything else with the disassemble or reassembly is all included. The only additional cost whatsoever is a one time $75 travel fee, and that's just to return our truck from that final address. The other than that travel fee there's no additional costs, it is just the time that it takes for us to move that time starts when we arrive and start moving that time stops once we have delivered and set up everything at the new place, one bedroom apartments normally take about three to four hours.",
